Table 2 shows the prerequisite courses and their prerequisites. For each of the five courses marked in light blue in the table,
design an algorithm that determines whether the student can take those courses.
Hint: Use the Table when you do your conditions (if/else system). Determination will be using 0 and 1 numbers. 
For instance, if the student passed MAT101, then make MAT101 equals to 1.
Let the student had fundamental courses which are MAT101, INF211, ELEC225, ELM231, MATH214, MAT215 (give them 0 or 1 values). 
By using fundamental courses, determine advanced courses states. Finally, find out the student can have ELEC416, ELEC418, ELEC421, ELEC425, ELEC426 or not. 

Table 2. The List of Some Prerequisite Courses

ÖN KOŞULLU DERS                                                     	 ÖN KOŞUL

